{"cursor":"3116","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox monarch |name = Chlodio |title = King of the Salian Franks |image=\nPortrait Roi de france Clodion.jpg |caption = Chlodio |reign = |coronation =\n|othertitles = |full name = Chlodio |native_lang1 = |native_lang1_name1=\n|native_lang8 = |native_lang8_name1= |predecessor = |successor = |suc-type =\n|heir = |queen = Basina (daughter of Wedelphus, an alleged king of the\nThuringii)  |consort = |offspring = Merovech (disputed)\n|royal house = |dynasty = |royal anthem = |father = Pharamond (disputed) |mother\n= Argotta (disputed) |birth_date = c. 392/395 |birth_place\n= |death_date = 445 /448 (~aged 50) |death_place = |date of\nburial = |place of burial =\n|}}\n\n'Chlodio' (c. 392/395 –445 /448; also spelled 'Clodio', 'Clodius', 'Clodion', 'Cloio' or 'Chlogio') was a\nking of the Salian Franks from the Merovingian dynasty. He was known as the Long-\nHaired King and lived in Thuringian territory, at the castle of Duisburg. He\nbecame chief of the ThÃ©rouanne area in 414 AD. From there, he invaded the Roman\nEmpire in 428, defeating a Roman force at Cambrai, and settled in Northern Gaul,\nwhere other groups of Salians were already settled. Although he was attacked by\nthe Romans, he was able to maintain his position and, 3 years later in 431, he\nextended his kingdom south to the Somme River in the future Francia. In\nAD 448, 20 years after his reign began, Chlodio was defeated at an\nunidentified place called Vicus Helena by Flavius AÃ«tius, the commander of the\nRoman army in Gaul.\n\nLike all Merovingian kings, Chlodio had long hair as a ritual custom. His\nsuccessor may have been Merovech, after whom the dynasty was named\n'Merovingian'. The non-contemporary [[Liber Historiae Francorum]] says his\nfather was Pharamond, whom many believe to have been a legendary person linked\nto the lineage sometime in the 8th century. The [[Chronicle of Fredegar]] makes\nChlodio son of Theudemeres, one of the leaders of the Salian Franks and king of\nThÃ©rouanne (409â414).\n","linknr":195,"url":"Clodio","recorded":1375070496,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Chlodio&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Chlodio&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Chlodio","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Clodio&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Salian_Franks","/wiki/File:Portrait_Roi_de_france_Clodion.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Portrait_Roi_de_france_Clodion.jpg/220px-Portrait_Roi_de_france_Clodion.jpg","#cite_note-Franks2-1","#cite_note-Franks2-1","/wiki/Thuringii","#cite_note-Franks2-1","/wiki/Pharamond","/w/index.php?title=Argotta&action=edit&redlink=1","#cite_note-Franks2-1","#cite_note-Franks2-1","/wiki/Salian_Franks","/wiki/Merovingian","/wiki/Dynasty","/wiki/Duisburg","/wiki/Th%C3%A9rouanne","/wiki/Roman_Empire","/wiki/Cambrai","/wiki/Gaul","/wiki/Somme_River","/wiki/Francia","/wiki/Flavius_A%C3%ABtius","/wiki/Military_history_of_the_Roman_Empire","/wiki/Merovingian_dynasty","/wiki/Merovech","/wiki/Liber_Historiae_Francorum","/wiki/Pharamond","/wiki/Chronicle_of_Fredegar","/wiki/Theudemeres","/w/index.php?title=Chlodio&action=edit&section=1","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.sv